args: Let's see... I think that's everything we\nneeded to buy, right?
Yes. Shall we head back to the castle?
Bwa ha ha! Too slow, kiddies!
What the...? He's gonna escape by SHIP?!
Blast! We'll not be able to secure him if he\nsets off down the river.
Huh? Your Highness, look over there!
Um...is that person running ON the water?
Then he spun through the air and landed\nbehind the purse-snatcher!
The heck's your deal, weirdo?! Lemme go!
I am Orsem, and I travel the world\npreaching the gospel of ice skating!
I know those words, but they don't make\nany sense in that order. Now get yer paws\noff'a me already!
What's not to understand? Skating is fun!
But before you can try it, you need to go\napologize to that woman.
It's not nice to take things from people\nby force.
Oh, they came back to shore!
Now go tell the local officials what you\ndid and beg them for clemency.
Thank you for returning my purse, sir!
Can you really run on the water, mister?
Ah ha ha! What I was doing earlier is\ncalled ＂skating!＂
Skating is a whirlwind of delight, and all\nwho are interested are welcome to come\nlearn the art with me!
Pretty impressive. But hey, tell me more\nabout this ＂skating＂ thing.
Wait, you're interested in skating?!\nThen come with me to the river!
Sir! You will unhand His Highness at once\nor answer to me for this outrage!
Oh man, this is six different kinds of\nincredible. I've never met a king before.
And hey! Since you're a king, you could\nhelp me make skating famous!
It's my dream to spread the joy of skating\nthroughout the whole world, see?
So go order your subjects to stop whatever\nthey're doing and SKATE!
Er, that's...not really how it works.
First I must tell you in excruciating detail\nwhat makes skating so great so that you\ncan spread its joys around the world.
So how about it? Can I come with you and\ntell you all about skating? It's okay, right?\nRiiiiiight?!
I, er... Well, that is to say... Sure?
YA-HOOOO! Now I'll be able to get people\nlaced up and skating the world over!
Are you sure we should invite him to the\ncastle, Highness? He seems quite mad.
I, um...  Well, I suppose it can't hurt to\nat least hear him out?
